Description: A low dish of pale red pottery, the surface covered by a pale cream slip. There is a projecting external rim and a low ring-foot.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 3
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 3 has been scratched into the object.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.92, fig.7, p.100, p.189, pl.31) (incorrectly given as 1887,1010.1300 on p.100)
Additional IDs: Miscellaneous number: 1887,0101.1300 (incorrect number given on p.100 of Leclère and Spencer 2014)
